  "title": "Infant Educator (North/East/West/Central)",
  "description": "<p><em>Our client is a nonprofit organization where they strive to make a meaningful impact in our community.</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop and implement age-appropriate programmes and teaching aids to support the growth of infants aged 2 to 18 months.</li>\n  <li>Maintain a safe, engaging, and conducive environment while fostering positive relationships with infants, parents, and colleagues.</li>\n  <li>Assess and document infants' progress, addressing their individual developmental needs.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with the Centre Principal on operational matters and ensure adherence to teaching standards and safety regulations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Advanced Certificate in Early Childhood Education.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of relevant working experience</li>\n  <li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills to build positive relationships with infants, parents, and colleagues.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
